The use of predicates and the ability to handle cycles also suggest that it may be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the drawbacks of the acyclic structure of Bayesian networks, which may make it relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
